	<h3>Naturally More Valuable </h3>
	<p>
		Not only is Natural Link Exchange free. It  makes your
		links more valuable than other link exchange schemes. It does this in several ways. Most importantly, Natural Links
		are added gradually so as not to trip the spam filter of the search engines. Just read the
		<a href="Extra-Content/Google-Patent-Secrets/">Google Patent</a>, it's quite obvious that Google is tracking the
		history of the growth of your website's link popularity. This single feature alone places Natural Link Exchange
		in an entirely different class than the crowd of "spammy" automated link exchange schemes.
	</p>
	<a href="Screenshots/"><img src="ScreenShots/ControlPanel.jpg" class="floatLeft" /></a>
	<p>
		As Natural Link Exchange adds your text links to other sites, it allows you full control of the link text as well
		as the frequency of distribution of each link text. You control these and several other attributes about your links
		using the Natural Link Exchange control panel.  You heard it right:  you easily control both the anchor
		text and the distribution of this link text (how many times a given link text appears on another site) for  your
		links that are located on sites that you don't have access to.
	</p>
	<p>For example, if you were selling widgets you might vary your anchor text as follows</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Great Widgets 60%</li><li>Blue Widgets 30%</li><li>Hot Pink Widgets 10% </li>
	</ul>
	
